 <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
 <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  There are several "right" ways to sign "snow."
  <br/>
  Here's my
  <i>
   recommended
  </i>
  way to sign it:
  <br/>
  Hold your hands up in the air
  <font face="Arial">
   . 
	Flutter your fingers as you move your hands down and side to side. (But, as 
	always, you should sign it however it is signed by your local Deaf or local 
	ASL instructor.)
  </font>
  <br/>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
   SNOW:
   <br/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow2.jpg" width="253"/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow3.jpg" width="253"/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow4.jpg" width="253"/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow5.jpg" width="253"/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow6.jpg" width="253"/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow7.jpg" width="253"/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow8.jpg" width="253"/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow9.jpg" width="253"/>
   <img border="0" height="224" src="../../signjpegs/s/snow10.jpg" width="253"/>
  </p>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
