  </font>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
   <br/>
   Notes:
   <br/>
   Some people touch their hands to their shoulders at the beginning of  
	the sign snow. I've never liked that version because it makes me think of 
	dandruff.
   <br/>
   <br/>
   Some people do the sign "
   <a href="../w/white.htm">
    WHITE
   </a>
   " at the beginning 
	of the sign "snow." I suppose that is to distinguish it from "yellow snow?"  
	-- Which could be a very helpful distinction if you happen to be
   <i>
    <a href="../t/thirsty.htm">
     thirsty
    </a>
   </i>
   .
  </p>
